          <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <h2 id="how-we-tested">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 6 noise canceling headphones based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing for ANC performance, build quality, comfort during long sessions, and value. Each product was assessed across identical workflow categories including writing, coding, and video calls.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled based on documentation and specification analysis. ANC effectiveness was assessed against manufacturer-published noise reduction data covering office ambiance, keyboard clatter, and HVAC hum.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — How well does the ANC cut low-frequency noise, and how natural does music sound?</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Materials, hinge durability, earcup padding longevity, and headband construction</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-to-performance ratio compared to alternatives at the same price tier</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — Pairing, controls, multipoint connection reliability, and charging convenience</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</h2>
